meanings.definition: To fulfill or carry out (a task or obligation) to a greater extent than required.
meanings.sent1: She always tries to overfulfil her duties at work by completing extra tasks.
meanings.sent2: The team managed to overfulfil the project requirements ahead of schedule.
meanings.sent3: It's like she's on a mission to overfulfil every assignment she gets!
meanings.sent4: His dedication to overfulfil his promises shines brightly in his actions.
meanings.sent5: The student's determination to overfulfil expectations sets a great example for others.

meanings.definition: To exceed or surpass (a goal or target).
meanings.sent1: The athlete trained hard to overfulfil his personal best in the upcoming race.
meanings.sent2: Their sales numbers consistently overfulfil the company's quarterly targets.
meanings.sent3: The cake was so delicious that it seemed to overfulfil everyone's dessert dreams!
meanings.sent4: Her laughter overfulfils the room, spreading joy to all who hear it.
meanings.sent5: The colors of the sunset overfulfil any artist's palette with their beauty.
